description:
We are looking for AI/ML Consultants, who wants to work for the European Institutions in Brussels.




 We are looking for a senior IT consultant with at least 1 year of ML, NLP, AI experience with Python or Java in a cloud environment










 Candidates need to be based in Belgium or willing to relocate to Brussels when coming from abroad.










 EU candidates are welcome to apply. Work permit is not provided.










 This position is also open for employees and freelancers. Candidates need to be fluent in English.










**Tasks and responsibilities** 



* Develop and maintain software applications in Natural Language Processing (NLP), Machine Learning (ML), and Artificial Intelligence (AI);
* Design and optimize machine learning systems and deep learning architectures;
* Collaborate with cross\-functional teams to integrate AI/ML solutions into existing products and processes;
* Define and implement IT architectures for NLP, ML, and AI solutions, ensuring alignment with master and meta\-data management concepts;
* Perform data preprocessing, feature engineering, and model evaluation to enhance performance;
* Stay updated with the latest advancements in AI/ML technologies and algorithms;
* Maintain and support AI\-deployed solutions on SaaS platforms such as AWS and Azure;
* Document architecture blueprints and align them with business requirements;









**Profile:** 



* Master or Bachelor degree;
* \+13 years of general IT experience.
* \+1 year of experience with Large Language Models (LLMs), text embeddings, tokenization, vectorization, machine learning, and deep learning;
* \+1 year of experience with of Python/Java/Containers (Docker/Kubernetes)/Cloud AI services (AWS, Azure);
* \+1 year of experience in the full lifecycle of natural language processing (NLP) systems and agile software development methodologies;
* \+1 year of experience in quality assurance and quality control for machine translation (MT), and experience with MT quality procedures, testing methodologies and tools, such as automatic quality metrics (BLEU scores and similar) and human evaluation of MT quality;
* Proven ability to conduct proof of concepts (PoCs) efficiently and effectively;
* Strong presentation skills for both technical and business audiences;
* High attention to quality standards and the ability to work in fast\-evolving cloud\-based environments;
* Strong written communication skills for technical documentation;
* Ability to actively participate in technical discussions and collaborate with diverse stakeholders;
* Fluent in English;



 Desirable Certifications (one or more of the following certifications are preferred):



* AWS Certifications: AWS Certified Machine Learning, AWS Certified Data Analytics, AWS Certified Solutions Architect;
* Microsoft Certifications: Azure AI Engineer Associate, Azure Data Scientist Associate, Azure Solutions Architect Expert;

Binance is a leading global blockchain ecosystem behind the world’s largest cryptocurrency exchange by trading volume and registered users. We are trusted by over 250 million people in 100\+ countries for our industry\-leading security, user fund transparency, trading engine speed, deep liquidity, and an unmatched portfolio of digital\-asset products. Binance offerings range from trading and finance to education, research, payments, institutional services, Web3 features, and more. We leverage the power of digital assets and blockchain to build an inclusive financial ecosystem to advance the freedom of money and improve financial access for people around the world. **About the Role**
This role sits at the intersection of quantitative finance, machine learning, and natural\-language understanding. You’ll leverage NLU techniques—like sentiment and intent analysis—to mine news and social media for trading signals, build and mathematically refine predictive models, and rigorously backtest and optimize your strategies to drive data\-driven investment decisions.
### **Responsibilities:**

* Responsible for the architecture design and core module development of LLM\-based AI Agent systems, including task planning, memory management, tool invocation, and workflow execution;
* Lead the development of a general\-purpose Agent platform capable of multi\-task coordination and multi\-agent collaboration, enhancing the usability and stability of large models in complex business scenarios;
* Leverage key technologies such as LLMs, RAG, vector search, and function calling to build intelligent systems with contextual understanding and knowledge injection capabilities;
* Develop evaluation systems and automated testing tools for Agent behavior to continuously optimize task completion rate, response quality, and reliability;
* Drive the application of AI Agents in vertical scenarios such as search, trading, deep analysis, and automated data engineering to unlock the full value of LLMs.

### **Requirements:**

* Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, Financial Engineering or a related discipline
* Solid understanding of LLM principles (e.g., Transformers) and their application in Agent systems, with end\-to\-end experience in building and launching intelligent agents;
* Proficiency in at least two mainstream open\-source Agent frameworks such as LangChain, AutoGen, LangGraph, ADK, LlamaIndex, Dify, CrewAI, or CAMEL, with a strong grasp of their internal architectures;
* Familiar with RAG (Retrieval\-Augmented Generation) and capable of designing and optimizing knowledge retrieval systems; experience with vector databases like Milvus or FAISS is required;
* Experience implementing key Agent modules including Tool Use, Task Planning, Memory Management, and understanding their integration in real\-world applications;
* Strong software engineering background, proficient in Python/Java, and familiar with client\-server architectures and MCP\-like communication protocols.

**Why Binance*** Shape the future with the world’s leading blockchain ecosystem
* Collaborate with world\-class talent in a user\-centric global organization with a flat structure
* Tackle unique, fast\-paced projects with autonomy in an innovative environment
* Thrive in a results\-driven workplace with opportunities for career growth and continuous learning
* Competitive salary and company benefits
* Work\-from\-home arrangement (the arrangement may vary depending on the work nature of the business team)



Binance is committed to being an equal opportunity employer. We believe that having a diverse workforce is fundamental to our success.*By submitting a job application, you confirm that you have read and agree to our* ***Candidate Privacy Notice****.*

